Sutherland Public Schools
April 10, 2016 at 8:07 PM ¬∑

If you or your kiddos enjoy the Halloween Walk, Easter Egg Hunt, Bicycle Safety, or the technology in the classrooms, I encourage you to come to the Anchor Club meeting tomorrow at 4:30 at the school (Board Room). The Anchor Club (Elementary PTO) is a wonderful organization of parents, teachers, and community volunteers who do so much for our school and community. There are no dues involved with the Anchor Club, just volunteering to help out periodically with events that benefit our children and our school. Our meeting tomorrow night will be a big meeting to decide the future of the Anchor Club which has been going strong for 11 years. If you wish to see the great things the Anchor Club provides continue, please come to our meeting tomorrow and show your support and desire to help. It TAKES A VILLAGE to provide these opportunities for our kids!

shared_text:
Sutherland Public Schools
September 3, 2014 at 11:54 AM ¬∑

Local Board Members Recognized

The Nebraska Association of School Boards (NASB), Board of Directors and staff, recognized the 2014 Award of Achievement recipients during the North Platte Region Meeting on Thursday, August 28, 2014. Recognized from the Sutherland School Board was Myron McCune (Level IV) and Ken Kennedy (Level III).

Board Members from across the state may participate in board development training throughout the year by attending workshops and conferences to help strengthen their role in governance, legislative advocacy, and stewardship of district resources in support of student achievement. In recognition of their volunteer time and commitment to education, the NASB Association commends continued participation and growth in knowledge and best practice governance.

Have a great day,
Anchor Club
